      "content": "Mixing diazepam with even a small amount of alcohol can still significantly increase the depressant effects on your central nervous system. This can lead to enhanced drowsiness, confusion, and slower reaction times, which could be dangerous, especially if you need to drive or operate machinery. It's better to stick with the prescribed dose of diazepam and explore other relaxation techniques or discuss alternative treatments with your doctor. The risk of adverse effects outweighs the perceived benefit of combining the two.",
      "source": "target",
